# ECS (feature.ecs)

## Package

`com.unity.feature.ecs` → `com.unity.entities@6.5.0` (Unity 6.5)

## Policy

- **Default gameplay** in this template: **MonoBehaviour** + `Game.Gameplay` / `Game.Core` (see `unity-core.mdc`)
- **ECS is opt-in**: use only when explicitly starting an Entities-based feature
- If using ECS:
  - Separate folder: `Assets/Game/Scripts/Runtime/Entities/` with its own asmdef referencing `Unity.Entities`
  - Do not mix `IComponentData` systems with UniRx UI bindings in the same class
  - Subscenes / baking: follow Unity Entities manual

## MCP

- **core** + **docs** (`unity_reflect` for Entities APIs) — **MCP-first** when Editor connected
- `manage_scene`, `manage_components`, `manage_gameobject`, `manage_prefabs` for subscenes/baking setup
- No dedicated ECS MCP group

## When to choose ECS

Large entity counts, simulation-heavy logic, DOTS rendering path — not required for template samples.
